article.headline: Presbyterian 77, Radford 64
article.story: RADFORD, Va. -- Al'Lonzo Coleman had a double-double and Khalid Mutakabbir scored 21 points to lead Presbyterian to a 77-64 win over Radford on Thursday night. The Blue Hose's Coleman had 23 points and 10 rebounds for his second straight double-double and 10th of the season. Eric Washington added 14 points for Presbyterian (13-15, 7-10), who has beaten Radford three straight times. Coleman made 11 of 13 free throws as the Blue Hose converted 25 of 29 as a team. Presbyterian also shot well from the field, making 55.8 percent (24 of 43). Presbyterian trailed by as many as seven points in the first half but held a double-digit lead for most of the final 7 minutes of the game. The Blue Hose outscored Radford 34-20 in the paint. Tolga Cerrah scored 14 points, R.J. Price added 13 and Javonte Green had 11 for the Highlanders (6-24, 2-15).
